#: ../../../devel/testing.rst:1341
msgid "AVOCADO_ALLOW_LARGE_STORAGE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/testing.rst:1342
msgid ""
"Tests which are going to fetch or produce assets considered *large* are not "
"going to run unless that ``AVOCADO_ALLOW_LARGE_STORAGE=1`` is exported on "
"the environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/testing.rst:1346
msgid ""
"The definition of *large* is a bit arbitrary here, but it usually means an "
"asset which occupies at least 1GB of size on disk when uncompressed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/testing.rst:1350
msgid "AVOCADO_ALLOW_UNTRUSTED_CODE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/testing.rst:1351
msgid ""
"There are tests which will boot a kernel image or firmware that can be "
"considered not safe to run on the developer's workstation, thus they are "
"skipped by default. The definition of *not safe* is also arbitrary but "
"usually it means a blob which either its source or build process aren't "
"public available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/testing.rst:1357
msgid ""
"You should export ``AVOCADO_ALLOW_UNTRUSTED_CODE=1`` on the environment in "
"order to allow tests which make use of those kind of assets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/testing.rst:1361
msgid "AVOCADO_TIMEOUT_EXPECTED"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../devel/testing.rst:1362
msgid ""
